# No emojis in product UI — use icons

Do not use Unicode emoji characters (for example colored circles or pictograph warning symbols) in user-facing React or Next.js UI, API messages shown to admins, or coordinator tools.

**Do:** Use Phosphor Icons or the project’s existing icon set (for example `@phosphor-icons/react`) with appropriate `size`, `weight`, and `className` for color and alerts.

**Do not:** Paste emojis into JSX text, toast strings, or alert copy as substitutes for icons.

Admin-only copy should follow the same rule unless the user explicitly asks for emoji in a specific string.
